 href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23166_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#166_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tYAY!  Phew.  No bouncing_co_ no collision-fighting_co_ ghost1/2 are almost atop one another_co_ part1 and part2 are butted properly_co_   Damn!  Hooooooo-ray.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSolve?  Don_t_t use Oimo joints on boxes/impostors smaller than 1x1x1.  That... was the solve. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI_t_m not sure if that is normal_co_ but that_t_s what fixed these bouncy-joints.  (Ghost1/2 will be invisible... for the end-result.  SO_co_ their size doesn_t_t matter to the scene/project.)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWe MIGHT come to discover that ONLY the joint_t_s shape2/body2 must be 1x1x1 or larger.  PERHAPS... that is why joint1c was working correctly the entire time.  Part2... is joint1c_t_s shape2/body2_co_ and it was ALWAYS bigger than 1x1x1 units.  Also_co_ I still have a TINY gap between part1 and part2.  So I STILL could be seeing SOME hinge stretch.  More on that below.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnother thing... it seems these .belongsTo hex values... are actually two 4-bit nibbles.  In other words_co_ there might be only 16 collision groups. (I originally thought 256). \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tExamples_dd_ _lt_br /_gt_\n\tLine 1326_dd_ part1 impostor _eq_ FE collision group_lt_br /_gt_\n\tLine 1338_dd_ part2 impostor _eq_ E0 collision group_lt_br /_gt_\n\tLine 1379_dd_ ghost1 impostor _eq_ D2 collision group_lt_br /_gt_\n\tLine 1399_dd_ ghost2 impostor _eq_ C3 collision group\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tEach grouping... changes BOTH digits of the hex values (both nibbles). \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIn earlier versions_co_ I kept the 2nd digit (least significant nibble) the same for all impostors.  During the _qt_re-overlap_qt_ aligning (tightening-up the joints until top of part2 butted against bottom of part1)... there appeared to be some _qt_fighting_qt_.  Violent physics motions.  Not really colliding_co_ but... _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23167_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_impostors trying to escape being inside each other_t_s volumes_lt_/a_gt_.  The unwanted motions seemed to disappear when I changed/varied all those least significant nibbles... in those .belongsTo parameters.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI will research this more... as the project advances_co_ if it does.  Phew... it_t_s great to see the H3J (build-it-yourself hinge3Joint from 3 stacked hingeJoints)... operating much more correctly.  Bonfire!  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNo hinge angle min/max values are set/tested_co_ yet.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI feel like I gave birth to a bulldozer.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_biggrin.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/biggrin@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Now_co_ it_t_s Miller Time.  Oh wait_co_ it_t_s only 7_dd_30 AM here in Michigan_t_s UP.  I better have some coffee royale_co_ instead.  YAY!  (Wingy dances around but almost poops his pants_co_ so he quits... and sits.)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_strong_gt_Interesting note_dd__lt_/strong_gt_  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/shape/Box.js#L37_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/shape/Box.js#L37_lt_/a_gt_  Notice that in Oimo... the width and height are used (along with density) in the calculation of the mass.  When I set my ghosts to gSize _eq_ .25_co_ and if THAT was used as a _qt_density_qt_ value by Oimo... then... hmm.  In lines 1105-1114 in my _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23166_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_PG #166_lt_/a_gt__co_ we see our Oimo plugin talking _t_density_t_.  hmm.  One wonders... if I had set SUPER-LOW (micro) mass values on the two ghosts_co_ would bouncy joints be gone?  hmm.  Anyway_co_ in Oimo_co_ it seems that size affects mass.  But still_co_ heavy mass should _lt_u_gt_not_lt_/u_gt_ _qt_stretch_qt_ (elasticize) a hinge joint.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-01-25T16:30:18Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHi again.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23168_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#168_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHere_co_ I went back to gSize _eq_ .25 (ghost1/2 size)... so I could get _lt_strong_gt_bouncy joints1a/1b issue_lt_/strong_gt_ to return.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tA keen eye can catch blue ghost2... momentarily separating from the top of part2... when you fast-click the pulsars and quasars... to get part2 moving aggressively.  This indicates that joint1c is ALSO doing _lt_u_gt__lt_em_gt_some_lt_/em_gt__lt_/u_gt_ stretching.  hmm.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI started thinking about _qt_spring_qt_ (aren_t_t we all?).  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  I think the _lt_em_gt_spring_lt_/em_gt_ native parameter is an array of two values... _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/LimitMotor.js#L24_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_a frequency and a dampingRatio_lt_/a_gt_.  Not sure_co_ though.  I need to read.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnyway_co_ in lines 1403/1404_co_ I set a freq and damp value_co_ and then I use those values in the _lt_em_gt_spring_lt_/em_gt_ native parameter... for all three hinge joints (lines 1414_co_ 1429_co_ and 1444).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI see no changes in hinge bounce_co_ no matter the values. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIt is likely that _qt_spring_qt_ is axial... matching the hinge_t_s main/connected axes.  A hinge spring appears to NEED a limitMotor.  This makes sense.  Essentially_co_ these are the springs on the swinging doors of old-west cowboy saloons.  Frequency is the speed of swinging_co_ and dampingRatio is the _qt_elasticity dissipation factor_qt_  (what did he say?)  heh.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAlthough pulsars and quasars are quite good at applying hinge-testing and min/max-angle-testing forces in our recent playgrounds_co_ _lt_u_gt__lt_strong_gt_motors_lt_/strong_gt__lt_/u_gt_ COULD apply much more-precise and gently-metered testing forces.  If you think about it_co_ _t_spring_t_ could be a _lt_u_gt_motor-control_lt_/u_gt_ _qt_pattern_t_ or _t_sequence_t_.  It runs the motor forward_co_ then backward_co_ then forward_co_ etc... just like a clock pendulum hinge.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tLater_co_ when we start _qt_tweaking_qt_ our _qt_range of motion_qt_ (ROM) angle limits on joint1a/1b/1c_co_ we might want to devise a ROM (range-of-motion) motor-control sequence (specifically for our purposes).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tEase-in and ease-out speed controls seem possible_co_ and likely handy.  The pulsars and quasars are _qt_apply force right now... BANG_qt_ (a bit hard to control).  Conversely_co_ ease-in/out motors... would allow for some real gentle and accurate hip testing_co_ eh?  We could even install some fancier GUI... hingeJoints that display their current rotation in degrees or radians.  Nice.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-01-25T23:31:10Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23169_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#169_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tCheck that out.  Sweet.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSmall ghosts - I_t_m at gSize _eq_ 0.25  (line 1362)... and things are looking nice and tight. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNear-perfect ghost1/ghost2 position overlay!  Near-perfect part1/part2 end-butting!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHow?  A mass of 40 on ghost1 and ghost2 (lines 1375 and 1394).  Cooooool!   Whooooda thunkit?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_u_gt_Not_lt_/u_gt_ micro-mass (as pondered 2 posts ago).  Instead_co_ MEGA-mass!   Go fig.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tTight and firm.  I like _t_em tight and firm.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_o_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_ohmy.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/ohmy@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_o_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_   Sorry for being so talkie.  I hope I_t_m not annoying anyone.  These adventures need to be chronicled.  Wingnut Chronicled  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"JohnK","Date":"2018-01-26T00:22:49Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tcongratulations on your  success and perseverance.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-01-27T13:57:49Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThanks JK_co_ that_t_s very kind of you to think/say.  JohnK... you certainly showed plenty of perseverance with your BJS docs re-org and fleshing.... with success_co_ too.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI_t_m simply trying to keep up with you.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__sm_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_wink.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/wink@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__sm_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnyway_co_ here is the first of the _qt_motor tests_qt_.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23173_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#173_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI locked-down ghost1/2 with 0 mass... just to keep them from spinning-around_co_ temporarily.  (lines 1219 &amp_sm_ 1238)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIn lines 1301-1343... I have a motor-testing area.  Currently_co_ I_t_m ONLY working-on joint1c motor_co_ which is a Z-motor on a Z-joint (lines _lt_strong_gt_1326-1342_lt_/strong_gt_).  It join(t)s ghost2... with part2.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAfter 3-seconds_co_ we _qt_fire-up the motor_qt_.  Easy to see what happens.  Femur/part2 lifts to 3.11 radians upperLimit_co_ at a motorSpeed (and direction) of .1_co_ and a maxForce of 45. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThen_co_ after a few more seconds... I execute line 1340_co_ which sets the maxForce to 0... allowing part2 to fall_co_ due to its gravity.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tFUN!!!  Try setting maxForce in line 1333... to 25_co_ and see the motor NOT have enough power to lift part2 to upperLimit.  MORE fun!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnyway_co_ this PG is a reasonably fun place to start experimenting with physics motors.  We_t_re doing it ALL with _qt_native_qt_ methods_co_ so far.  BUT...  we still want to learn about the _lt_em_gt_spring_lt_/em_gt_ native parameter and its frequency and dampingRatio values_co_ if that_t_s what they are.   Reference_dd_  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/LimitMotor.js_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/LimitMotor.js_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAgain_co_ it is my theory... that _lt_em_gt_spring_lt_/em_gt_ and its frequency and dampingRatio values... is a motor controller.  Motor speeds and max forces... might be ignored... when the spring is activated.  Stay tuned... spring is coming.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Experiments and discoveries welcomed... wholeheartedly.  Motor on!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_strong_gt_New widget thoughts_dd__lt_/strong_gt_  I might need a new PhysicsTools widget.  Let_t_s see... we have pulsars (pulsing arrows)_co_ quasars (quaternion symmetrical axial rotaters)_co_ and now we need... umm... what?  Motars?  _lt_u_gt_MOT_lt_/u_gt_orized _lt_u_gt_A_lt_/u_gt_xial _lt_u_gt_R_lt_/u_gt_otaters?  heh. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tMotars would be the first widget for joints.  Pulsars and quasars are for mesh/impostors.  Probably only 2 buttons on a MOTAR... motor forward and motor backward buttons.  But we could use some on-widget adjust-ability for upper/lower limits_co_ and maxForce.  Three GUI drag-sliders and two GUI buttons?  Maybe.  But there is no mesh to GUI-track... only a joint.  SO... it also probably needs a label... telling WHICH JOINT any displayed motar... is bound-to. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSo_co_ label_co_ upperLimit slider_co_ lowerLimit slider_co_ maxPower slider_co_ forward and backward motor RUN buttons.  Anyone got that built for me_co_ yet?  huh?  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-02-01T01:26:57Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHi kids.  Uncle Wingnut here... with another episode of _qt_let_t_s motorize a hip joint_qt_  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23176_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#176_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tMotor-work happening in lines 1358 - 1373.  \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIn our last episode_co_ we _qt_lifted_qt_ (motored) the red femur around the z-axis (joint1c).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThis time_co_ I_t_m trying to _qt_lift_qt_ the red femur around the X axis (joint1a) (femur moves away-from camera)... but...  I had to _qt_unlock_qt_ ghost1 and ghost2... to make joint1a operational.  Unlock ghosts _eq_ set their mass to 40.  Lock_dd_ mass _eq_ 0.  The motor works fine (after 3 seconds) (1.5 motorSpeed is a little _qt_hot_qt_) but... I can_t_t seem to _qt_lock_qt_ the Y-joint (joint1b) from spinning. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIn other words_co_ I_t_m not getting a clean linear leg-lift with the motor.  It gets all weeble-wobble.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Set a .15 motorSpeed in line 1371... and you can more-easily see the unwanted spin-around after the motor starts running.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSo_co_ I went touring around in Oimo source... looking for an _qt_enabled/disabled_qt_ on joints.  None found.  But_co_ while I was there... I saw...\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/Joint.js#L192_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/Joint.js#L192_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tA getPosition function on a joint!  Not working for BJSOimo_co_ yet... but... getting the position of joints... WAS one of the BIGGEST problems... in a project to build a GUI layer... that automatically labels all the impostors and joints in ANY physics scene.  (cool project_co_ eh?)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tscene.showPhysicsInfo _eq_ true_sm_  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_   That would be great!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tjoint.getPosition() would be VERY handy in that project_co_ should someone decide to try to code it (with an AdvancedDynamicTexture_co_ surely).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tOk_co_ that_t_s it for this episode.  Trying to stop CERTAIN joints from wobbling-around... while trying to run a simple motor on a _lt_u_gt_different_lt_/u_gt_ joint...  not easy_co_ so far (for our H3J stack of 3 hinges atop each other_co_ each with a different axes).  Ahh... the home-built H3J... what an adventure it has been.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI think I saw a _qt_physicsHelpers_qt_ class/thing in BJS source_co_ the other day.  What the heck is that thing?  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  I think it might be a good place to put pulsars_co_ quasars_co_ and... motars (if they ever get invented).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tRight now_co_ I could use Babylon.PhysicsHelpers.JointBeStill(joint)  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Weeble on!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-02-02T10:12:07Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHi gang.  Continuing our physics project... I went looking-for information about HOW to _qt_lock-up_qt_ certain joints (with or without using a limitMotor to do it).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWhile I was touring Oimo basic hinge joint code... I found this... _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/HingeJoint.js#L52_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/HingeJoint.js#L52_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tRemember when we talked about _qt_r3_qt_ earlier?  Rotational3Contraint! \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnd look at line 52_co_ there.  The parameters for creating a new Rotational3Constraint... contains THREE limitMotors!  So_co_ let_t_s go look at the code for an Oimo r3c... _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThat is one big chunk of code_co_ eh?  erf.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBut_co_ the important thing is... a _lt_u_gt__lt_strong_gt_SINGLE_lt_/strong_gt__lt_/u_gt_ Oimo hinge joint... creates an r3c.  That r3c... has 3 limitMotors_co_ each having a ton of power/knobs.  Are you thinkin_t_ what I_t_m thinkin_t_?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tJust possibly_co_ with wise limitMotor controlling... we can eliminate 2 joints and 2 ghost mesh... and use a SINGLE Oimo hinge for our hip.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHaving a single hinge joint in each joint of a ragdoll... would sure make our life much simpler.  For each of those single hinge joints... we could _qt_program_qt_ the r3c_t_s 3 limitMotors... to _qt_act like a hip_qt__co_ or _qt_act like a knee_qt_.  Essentially_co_ we build a type of _qt_r3c programming language_qt_.  More likely_co_ it would be _qt_advanced joint config data_qt_.  Our physics systems already use joint configData... but it is not (yet) designed to send parameters/values to an Oimo hinge_t_s r3c object.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t(Actually_co_ our Oimo joint configData DOES install values into the joint_t_s r3c_co_ but ONLY into its FIRST (default) limitMotor.)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSo_co_ this is a new development and something worth thinking-about.  In the r3c source code... did you see how many properties are available?  Quite a few_co_ but most of them are already familiar to us... from our recent motor experiments.  But_co_ there are 3 properties there... of great interest to us_dd_  enableMotor1_co_ 2_co_ and 3.  YUM!  Still_co_ I am in question as-to... DOES a disabled axis-motor... LOCK IN PLACE?  Or does it release for completely-free pivoting?  Can it do EITHER... our choice?  YUM!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tPerhaps_co_ to _qt_lock_qt_ an axis/motor_co_ it needs to be enabled_co_ and have plenty of motor speed/maxForce... but have ZERO allowance in upperLimit and lowerLimit values.  In other words_co_ the motor is running strong and fast_co_ with upper/lower angle limits of 0.  Is THAT how we lock an r3c axis motor?  (I_t_ll try enableMotor2 first_co_ of course.)  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_biggrin.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/biggrin@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI suppose _lt_s_gt_we_lt_/s_gt_ I will need to find-out.  I guess it starts with designing _qt_advanced jointConfigData_qt_... and doing even MORE hacking on this custom Oimo plugin that we have been hauling from PG version to PG version.  Yay for r3c_t_s on Oimo hingeJoints_co_ though_co_ eh?  I wanted one to be on a ball-and-socket joint_co_ but what the heck. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_pre_gt_\n_lt_code_gt_this.r3 _eq_ new Rotational3Constraint( this_co_ this.limitMotor_co_ new LimitMotor( this.tan_co_ true )_co_ new LimitMotor( this.bin_co_ true ) )_sm__lt_/code_gt__lt_/pre_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNotice that the r3c parameters... use the already-installed this.limitMotor_co_ and then add 2-more limitMotors.  Those _qt_2-more_qt_ are the important part.  (_t_bin_t_ stands-for _t_binaryAngle_t_ as best I can tell.  Not sure.)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tJust possibly_co_ this is how the hinge joint does its stuff all the time.  These 2-more motors... are currently set _qt_locked-up_qt_... ie.  no pivoting allowed... around those two axes (a normal single-axis hinge).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBut_co_ by _qt_messing-with_qt_ those 2-more motors... maybe I can make this single-axis hinge... do ANYTHING I WISH?  hmm.  This includes... having 3 active axes/motors instead of 1_co_ and each using different lower/upper angle limits (a perfect hip joint).  Yum again!  hmm.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tDid ya see the _qt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js#L520_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_clamp state_lt_/a_gt__qt_ stuff at the bottom of the r3c source code?  See the _qt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js#L315_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_build jacobians_lt_/a_gt__qt_ section?  This is THE meat_t_n_t_potatoes of the Oimo hingeJoint here_co_ baby.  God-code.  Phew.  New adventures ahead.  Rotate on!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-02-03T02:23:15Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHi gang... same subject... the hippy joint.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23184_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#184_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tChanged to a 1-hinge system (OMG)... and... using the 3 motors (x_co_ y_co_ and z) contained on the hingeJoint_t_s _lt_strong_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/HingeJoint.js#L52_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_r3_lt_/a_gt__lt_/strong_gt_c (_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_rotational3constraint_lt_/a_gt_) has been successful so far.  Even though it is a one-axis hinge joint_co_ its 3 limit motors seem to work fine.  There_t_s a certain way of activating them... that works best.  We_t_ll talk about that later.  I_t_m still experimenting. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tCurrently_co_ lines 1239-1243 turns ON the X-axis motor_co_ and 12 seconds later... lines 1272-1278 turns it off.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI wish our red femur would _qt_swing freely_qt_ back and forth when the motor turns-off (and when maxMotorForce goes to zero)... but instead_co_ it sort of _qt_eases_qt_ back to down-position.  I_t_ll study it more.  R3C calls such as... joint1a._physicsJoint._lt_strong_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/HingeJoint.js#L52_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_r3_lt_/a_gt__lt_/strong_gt_._lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js#L62_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_enableMotor1_lt_/a_gt_ _eq_ false_sm_  ...have not worked real well_co_ but I am early in the tests and mistakes are likely.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnd_co_ of course_co_ you can_t_t miss the brand new GUI... painfully built in lines 1384-1678.  The R3C Motor Controller!  YAY!  (a _t_motar_t_?)  (I don_t_t really like that name... its not as cool as quasars and pulsars.)  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_biggrin.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/biggrin@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThis new _t_motar_t_ GUI is _lt_u_gt_not wired-up_lt_/u_gt_ yet_co_ but it_t_s getting near. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tLikely_co_ it needs more controls_co_ yet.  I think I will need a motorSpeed and maxMotorForce sliders... for each axis.  SO_co_ one more slider and one more label... per line_co_ I guess (gettin_t_ wide).  The current sliders will probably be motorSpeed and the slider _qt_puck_qt_ will likely be centered.  Drag it left... motor runs one way_co_ drag it right... the other way.  That_t_s tomorrow_t_s project. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI might use 2-3 stacked sliders just like now_co_ but instead of one for each axis... perhaps use checkBoxes to select _qt_Which axis?_qt_  That will save me some _qt_real estate_qt_ space... keep the panel smaller_co_ maybe.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBrand new stuff... with promising indicators.  I tried using the motors on all three axes of this single hinge joint_co_ and they all worked fine... WITHOUT needing to lock any of the other axes (no spin-around problems.  Spin-around was a problem that was left behind when I returned to a single hinge joint and no ghosts). \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAll good news_co_ but keep in mind... that just because motors work on all three axes of this single hinge_co_ it doesn_t_t mean that it will _lt_strong_gt_act like a human hip_lt_/strong_gt_ when we smack our ragdoll with a beer truck.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_biggrin.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/biggrin@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_D_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_ \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tMotors are one thing... but forces imposed by beer truck bumpers... is a different thing.  Party on!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-02-03T16:52:58Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHi girls. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_strong_gt_Another Update_dd_  _lt_/strong_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23185_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#185_lt_/a_gt__lt_strong_gt_  _lt_/strong_gt_Motor sliders_lt_strong_gt_ _lt_/strong_gt_operational_co_ somewhat.  In lines 1492-1493_co_ change Math.PI to Math.PI/2 (or some smaller values).  RUN_co_ and use X-slider.  Notice how red mesh disappears when it hits an upper/lower angle limit?  hmm.  What the heck?  *scratch scratch* \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAlso_co_ I_t_ve been thinking about _qt_motorImpulse_qt_ and _qt_maxMotorImpulse_qt_... as seen _lt_strong_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js#L299_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_here_lt_/a_gt__lt_/strong_gt_.  We should probably be careful in our thinking_co_ here.  Likely_co_ _qt_joint impulsing_qt_... is completely different from impostor impulsing_co_ yet both are still... MOMENTARY or INSTANT force_co_ and then stop.  Hammer-hit.  Other interesting properties in that area... _lt_em_gt_limitState_co_ limitVelocity_lt_/em_gt__co_ and _lt_em_gt_enableSpring._lt_/em_gt_  hmm.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tMaybe... when using impulsing... joints are allowed to swing back and forth freely (let_t_s call it _lt_span style_eq__qt_color_dd_#c0392b_sm__qt__gt_free-wheeling_lt_/span_gt_) after the impulse completes.  That sounds like something a _lt_em_gt_spring_lt_/em_gt_ might need_co_ eh?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tFree-wheeling is something I seek_co_ sometimes_co_ for _lt_u_gt_after_lt_/u_gt_ a motor is shut-off.  Continued spinning after motor disengaged_co_ due-to momentum/mass/inertia.   I have much to learn_co_ yet.  There is a difference between force-less motoring (dynamic braking or _t__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compression_release_engine_brake_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_jake braking_lt_/a_gt__t_)... and motor completely-disengaged (neutral gear _t_coasting_t_)_co_ in both real life_co_ and maybe in Oimo_co_ as well.  In an earlier post_co_ I mentioned that the mesh _qt_eases_qt_ back to downward position (after motor forces removed).  That... is a _qt_jake-braking_qt_ indication_co_ somewhat.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tMoving on...\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSlider-&gt_sm_motorSpeed _qt_bindings_qt_... happen at lines 1490_co_ 1583_co_ and 1677 ... all slider onChange observers.  All maxMotorForce set to 25000.  FUN!!!   \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThere is a problem when X or Z sliders are dragged to their minimum/maximum.  Reason unknown_co_ still.  Overall motor _qt_power_qt_ is calculated with some kind of formula... using both _lt_em_gt_motorSpeed_lt_/em_gt_ and _lt_em_gt_maxMotorForce_lt_/em_gt_ values.  I haven_t_t studied it well_co_ yet.  Perhaps motorSpeeds (slider values) of &gt_sm_ 2.0 or &lt_sm_ 2.0... somehow crash that _qt_overall power_qt_ calculation/formula.  Needs study.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnd_co_ I still get some _qt_physics violence_qt_  when multiple motors run at the same time_co_ or run in certain sequences.  Still learning.  I dislike physics violence/spasms.  It makes my mesh... dizzy_co_ and motion-sick.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_qt_I_t_m so dizzy_co_ my mesh is spinnin_t_.  Like a whirlpool... it never ends._qt_ - _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.youtube.com/watch?v_eq_sbdtQ99yIUo_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_Tommy Roe_lt_/a_gt_.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_strong_gt_Yet another update_dd_ _lt_/strong_gt_ _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23190_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#190_lt_/a_gt_  Added features to the R3C motor GUI panel.  You can now click on the red labels.  Click _lt_u_gt_left side_lt_/u_gt_ (of any red label)... you get an impulse that _qt_works_qt_ THAT axis... with a NEGATIVE impulse (upon part2 mesh).  Click _lt_u_gt_right side_lt_/u_gt_ of a red label_co_ you get a POSITIVE impulse.  _lt_u_gt_HOW FAR_lt_/u_gt_ left/right that you click upon any red label... determines the FORCE LEVEL of that impulse.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIt is nice to see _qt_free-wheeling_qt_ (pendulum swinging) still working_co_ but all motors are shut-off for these click-on-label impulsings.  The impulsings are NOT currently _qt_motor/hinge impulsings_qt_.  They are impulsings upon the part2 impostor itself.   BUT... _lt_strong_gt_ARE_lt_/strong_gt_ all motors shut-off when pendulum-swing free-wheeling?  Continuous logging of limitMotor _lt_em_gt_angle _lt_/em_gt_property... during impulse pendulum-swing... shows values alternating between -1 and +1... matching the swing-rate.  Do the limitMotors (with the help of R3C) actually CAUSE/CREATE the pendulum swinging?  I_t_m thinkin_t_ _qt_YES_qt_.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tEven _lt_strong_gt_IF_lt_/strong_gt_ the motors are being used for the impulsings_co_ none of the motor upper/lower limits... are active/working.  (oh no!)  Wingnut mistakes likely.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tFor a proper hip joint... we need the impulsings to free-wheel (until muscles and tendons are added)_co_ but we still _lt_u_gt_need_lt_/u_gt_ angle limits... 6 of them_co_ total. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWe need the femur to flop-around as it tumbles down the road after our ragdoll is hit by a beer truck.  But we need that _qt_flop-around_qt_ to happen within the angle limits of a human hip (at least until the pelvic bones shatter - yum). \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tMin/Max angles on each axis... while still maintaining free-wheeling... is the objective.  The only reason I am doing work on motors at all... is to TRY to have a system to accurately/precisely test angle-limits.  But perhaps I _lt_u_gt_NEED_lt_/u_gt_ motors to do _lt_u_gt_ANY_lt_/u_gt_ angle limits_co_ whether for free-wheeling impulses_co_ or for motorized hinge movements.  Currently_co_ when a motorized hinge axis (an R3C axis)... hits an upper/lower limit... red part2 disappears.  Not sure why.  Un-wanted thing_co_ of course.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNew _lt_strong_gt_Reset_lt_/strong_gt_ button currently doesn_t_t reset motor sliders/values - only the label-click impulsings.  More experiments/learning ahead.  Party on!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-02-05T16:56:10Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t*sigh*  Yet another.  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH%23194_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1ND6TH#194_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tLots of features being added to the R3C (rotational3constraint) Motor Controller.  Now_co_ mouseover label-change on the red labels. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tReminder_dd_ red label clicks produce applyImpulse actions on part2 femur - location sensitive - clicks on far-left side of label produces large NEGATIVE impulses_co_ far right side clicks... large POSITIVE impulses..\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWhy Z impulse for X label_co_ and X impulse for Z label?  Because...  part2 needs a Z-direction impulse... to make it rotate around X-axis of hinge. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSame for last label.  To make Z hinge joint operate_co_ part2 needs an X-direction impulsing. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAll 3 red labels are _qt_variable-value dual-direction impulsers_qt_... when clicked.  Fast-clicking allowed_co_ too.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAlso_co_ you_t_ll see 3 more _qt_lines_qt_ added to the motor controller.  These are real-time readouts from the limitMotor _lt_em_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/lo-th/Oimo.js/blob/gh-pages/src/constraint/joint/base/Rotational3Constraint.js#L191_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_angle_lt_/a_gt__lt_/em_gt_ values (a read-only property_co_ as far as I know).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tA renderLoop wedge powers the _lt_em_gt_angle_lt_/em_gt_ readouts... in lines 2201-2206.  s1label_co_ s2label_co_ and s3label onPointerDownObservables... is where the click-on-red-label impulsers are coded.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNot very exciting_co_ huh?  But do some red-label impulsings and watch the angle readouts.  VERY unexpected behaviors from the angle readouts.  At first_co_ it fooled me into thinking that I _qt_bound_qt_ the wrong displays to the motor-angle values.  But nope_co_ triple verified. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tA click on the top red label... makes the X AND Z angles swing/activate.  (limitMotor1 and limitMotor3)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tA click on the bottom red label_co_ makes the Y angle readout activate.  (limitMotor2)   Strange.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThe middle red button is slightly different.  It does a dual-impulse _qt_twist_qt_ to make part2 spin-around the Y axis.  Yet... the X-angle (limitMotor1) display... goes active.  But watch the Y and Z angle values.  They are active_co_ too_co_ toggling their signs_co_ yet staying at 0.000.  Weird. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tRemember_co_ the RESET button doesn_t_t properly reset the scene... when sliders are used.  Re-RUN to reset... after slider-usage.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWho would EVER suspect... that there is THIS MUCH TO LEARN... about a darned Oimo hinge joint_co_ eh?  It is like a mid-sized city!  SO MUCH to explore!  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Fun!  (and scary!)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-02-11T01:21:16Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHi gang!  Hey_co_ I took a break from joints work... to play-with another project that I started earlier... sparkly GUI fonts.  (coooool).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tEarlier_co_ I thought I had everything I needed.  I was grabbing the context2d _qt_canvas_qt_ (image buffer) that was used for the text.  Then I set EVERY pixel in that image... that had an .alpha &gt_sm_0... to a random color.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBut_co_ I could not figure out how to tell the advancedDynamicTexture (ADT)... to update to the NEW image buffer colors. Well_co_ I figured that out.  (line 224)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV%2351_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV#51_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tOther things_dd_  I had to _qt_hijack_qt_ two framework functions into my playground... ADT._render_co_ and a helper object IT needed... called Measure.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tShe_t_s pretty slow.  The paintIt() call in the renderLoop line 240... is a rather heavy load... considering it repaints the entire createdForMesh ADT canvas... once per frame.  (erf!)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThe canvas dimensions in line 85... are quite important_co_ speed-wise.  Feel free to adjust them_co_ but be prepared to adjust fontSize in line 96... after adjustments to dimensions.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThis same method can be used on standard dynamicTextures_co_ too_co_ so the entire surface of a mesh... can do these _qt_sparkles_qt__co_ too.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBUT... shaders seem to animate materials better than ANYTHING my blit-animator can do.  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#TZSWRR%232_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#TZSWRR#2_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThat_t_s the _qt_lava material_qt_.  If we still have a _qt_fire material_qt_... I think that has equally smooth animation.  That would look great... inside our fonts_co_ eh?  Yum.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSo_co_ maybe_co_ _lt_span_gt__lt_a contenteditable_eq__qt_false_qt_ data-ipshover_eq__qt__qt_ data-ipshover-target_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/13038-nasimiasl/?do_eq_hovercard_qt_ data-mentionid_eq__qt_13038_qt_ href_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/13038-nasimiasl/_qt_ rel_eq__qt__qt__gt_@NasimiAsl_lt_/a_gt_ or some other shader Gods... will show us how to do sparklies... with a shader (for mesh materials_co_ not GUI context2d stuff)._lt_/span_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_span_gt_Ideally_co_ though... it would be nice to have MANY quick-adjust _qt_sparkle-styles_qt__lt_/span_gt_ to _qt_plug-into_qt_ the shader.  AND... bad news.  Since GUI fonts/controls/borders are NOT a mesh and don_t_t use a material_co_ we will still need a different method... to sparkle-animate GUI things.  I don_t_t think GUI canvas-items are made-for post-processes or shaders... (yet)  (ahem).\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAll in all_co_ I_t_m glad to see my CPU-heavy GUI font-sparkler... doing some sparkling.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Also_co_ that _qt_font canvas_qt_ doesn_t_t NEED to animate_co_ and can also be filled-with still-pic patterns (fake reflections of images inside the fonts)_co_ dynamic-genned fractal patterns_co_ lace_co_ fish scales_co_ alligator-skin_co_ bubbles_co_ etc.  Even frames of video_co_ I think.  Your fonts can have ANY _qt_fill_qt_.  Your imagination is the only limit. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHave a great weekend_co_ everyone!  Party on!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_strong_gt_Update_dd__lt_/strong_gt_  It was like pulling teeth_co_ but I finally got a loaded image (non-animated)... to be the _lt_strong_gt_fill_lt_/strong_gt_ of the fonts_dd_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV%2356_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV#56_lt_/a_gt_  Some water rings.  Exciting. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tPerhaps we can convince DeltaDawn to permanently add _qt_fill image_qt_ to ALL of our textBlock controls_co_ huh?   _lt_img alt_eq__qt__sm_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_wink.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/wink@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__sm_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  (I treat him like he_t_s my techno-slave_co_ don_t_t I?  *nod*  Pathetic_co_ I am.)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tFill images/patterns (both dynamic-generated and/or static-loaded) seem to work best... on fat/thick fonts_co_ such as Impact font.  Notice the _lt_strong_gt_text1.lineSpacing _eq_ -15_sm_ _lt_/strong_gt_in line 102?  Yep.  That is for helping me fill LOTS of screen space... with fonts/text.  Try some _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.google.com/search?q_eq_horizon+wikimedia&amp_sm_tbs_eq_sur_dd_fc_co_isz_dd_m&amp_sm_tbm_eq_isch&amp_sm_source_eq_lnt&amp_sm_sa_eq_X&amp_sm_ved_eq_0ahUKEwi3g_bPnp7ZAhUE4GMKHeCSB8IQpwUIHg&amp_sm_biw_eq_1216&amp_sm_bih_eq_625&amp_sm_dpr_eq_1.58_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_horizons_lt_/a_gt_ or _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.google.com/search?q_eq_cityscape+wikimedia&amp_sm_tbs_eq_sur_dd_fc_co_isz_dd_m&amp_sm_tbm_eq_isch&amp_sm_source_eq_lnt&amp_sm_sa_eq_X&amp_sm_ved_eq_0ahUKEwi3g_bPnp7ZAhUE4GMKHeCSB8IQpwUIHg&amp_sm_biw_eq_1216&amp_sm_bih_eq_625&amp_sm_dpr_eq_1.58_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_cityscape_lt_/a_gt_ textures for the URL in line 216.   [_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV%2354_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_pg#54_lt_/a_gt_ is a horizon demo]   You_t_ll see... that it is sometimes difficult to _qt_make out_qt_ the picture that is filling the fonts.  *shrug*  New stuff - still learning.  FUN!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-02-20T14:59:38Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tYay_co_ sparticles (sparkly particles) are working again.  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#UP2O8%2340_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#UP2O8#40_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t(Wingy dances around like a chicken).  There was a little bug that DeltaFlyer fixed for us.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnother_co_ you say?  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//playground.babylonjs.com/#36UHXZ%2324_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//playground.babylonjs.com/#36UHXZ#24_lt_/a_gt_   (Recently updated to utilize the new non-offsetting setPivotMatrix feature.)  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__sm_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_wink.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/wink@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__sm_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  (might be memory-leaky or somehow CPU-heavy)\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tFireworks junkies.  That_t_s what I and all glitter-addicts... really are.  I love fireworks.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAnother one?  Ok.  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1NXKLI%2313_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#1NXKLI#13_lt_/a_gt_  6-planes with PS emitbox covering entire plane.  Strange_co_ fun stuff.  Glitter generators... YAY!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tOkay_co_ time to get to work.  In our last episode_co_ we put a picture inside the GUI fonts... _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV%2359_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV#59_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWe also did some VERY FPS-SLOW color speckles inside the fonts.  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV%2352_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV#52_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThe real fun... is in mixing _qt_sparticles_qt_... with the GUI.  Here is my first attempt.  Just a plane-shaped _t_emitBox_qt_ behind our message...\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV%2360_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV#60_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI am still too scared to try repeatedly-painting a renderTargetTexture of the panel-o-sparticles... INSIDE the fonts.  But a guy COULD (i think)!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBack to our image of water rings... INSIDE the fonts.  _lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV%2361_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_https_dd_//www.babylonjs-playground.com/#11JINV#61_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThis time_co_ I have turned-on line 304... which makes the image paint into the fonts over and over.  Look at the frame rates.  Pretty muddy_co_ eh?  *nod*\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSubtract another 10%_co_ and we can predict the frame rate... IF we ever decided to grab the sparticles panel into a renderTargetTexture_co_ and use THAT as our ANIMATED inside-the-fonts image.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSparticles... INSIDE THE FONTS!  How cool would that be?   Perhaps I don_t_t care HOW SLOW that would be_co_ I may need to see it done... out of pure curiosity.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSo_co_ who is a pro at renderTargetTextures?  Are there OTHER ways of showing the sparticles (sparkly particles) from PG#60... INSIDE the fonts ONLY?  Layermasking or renderGroups or blendingModes or some other complicated thing?  I would LOVE to see fully-animated sparticles... INSIDE the font volumes.   Anyone want to try it?  (please). \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI need to woof a bowl of Ralston and go do some snowblowing.  We got a little snow last night_co_ and the mailperson paths and driveway... need cleaning.  Ahh_co_ thank goodness spring is near.  Snow is fun_co_ but sometimes it lasts too many months.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_   Snowblow on!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2018-04-02T16:17:09Z","C